cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.CL 

The paper deals with organizing and segmenting egocentric photo streams using Convolutional Neural Networks and semantic information. This involves computer vision (cs.CV) techniques for image analysis, machine learning (cs.MM) for clustering and segmentation, information retrieval (cs.IR) for indexing and retrieval, and natural language processing (cs.CL) for defining a vocabulary of concepts. The use of semantic information also suggests the possibility of incorporating techniques from computational linguistics (cs.CL) and the regularization approach used in the clustering algorithm could be related to work in machine learning (cs.LG).
